Objet : Re: [T2]Copper gasket seals /exhaust leak problems????


It's hard to get the manifolds to seat correctly, especially if you've
done some brazing. The pipes tend to warp anyway from exhaust heat,
and you generally have to file the tops of the manifolds to get them
flat again, and then carefully tighten the manifolds onto the head to
get a good seal.

John
